			
			Assignment –6
		Using Special Operators in Conditions.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q 1) Write two different queries that would produce all orders taken on October 3 rd or
	4 th , 1990.

ans)->
	1)mysql> select * from orders where Odate  between '1990-10-03' and '1990-10-04';

	 +------+---------+------------+------+------+
	 | Onum | Amt     | Odate      | Cnum | Snum |
	 +------+---------+------------+------+------+
	 | 3001 |   18.69 | 1990-10-03 | 2008 | 1007 |
	 | 3002 | 1900.10 | 1990-10-03 | 2007 | 1004 |
	 | 3003 |  767.19 | 1990-10-03 | 2001 | 1001 |
	 | 3005 | 5160.45 | 1990-10-03 | 2003 | 1002 |
	 | 3006 | 1098.16 | 1990-10-03 | 2008 | 1007 |
	 | 3007 |   75.75 | 1990-10-04 | 2004 | 1002 |
	 | 3009 | 1713.23 | 1990-10-04 | 2002 | 1003 |
	 +------+---------+------------+------+------+

ans)->
	2)mysql> select * from orders where Odate >= '1990-10-03' and Odate <= '1990-10-04';
	
	+------+---------+------------+------+------+
	| Onum | Amt     | Odate      | Cnum | Snum |
	+------+---------+------------+------+------+
	| 3001 |   18.69 | 1990-10-03 | 2008 | 1007 |
	| 3002 | 1900.10 | 1990-10-03 | 2007 | 1004 |
	| 3003 |  767.19 | 1990-10-03 | 2001 | 1001 |
	| 3005 | 5160.45 | 1990-10-03 | 2003 | 1002 |
	| 3006 | 1098.16 | 1990-10-03 | 2008 | 1007 |
	| 3007 |   75.75 | 1990-10-04 | 2004 | 1002 |
	| 3009 | 1713.23 | 1990-10-04 | 2002 | 1003 |
	+------+---------+------------+------+------+

